pokemonDataList.name: Bulbasaur
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: For some time after its birth, it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.

pokemonDataList.name: Ivysaur
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.

pokemonDataList.name: Venusaur
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

pokemonDataList.name: Charmander
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

pokemonDataList.name: Charmeleon
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

pokemonDataList.name: Charizard
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

pokemonDataList.name: Squirtle
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

pokemonDataList.name: Wartortle
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

pokemonDataList.name: Blastoise
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

pokemonDataList.name: Chikorita
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun's rays.

pokemonDataList.name: Cyndaquil
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: It is timid, and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

pokemonDataList.name: Totodile
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.

pokemonDataList.name: Scizor
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Scizor's wings are not only for show. They can slice through a steel bar with ease. Its claws can rip through the toughest of materials.

pokemonDataList.name: Treecko
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Treecko is an agile Pokémon that can run up trees with ease. It lives in forests with lots of trees.

pokemonDataList.name: Grovyle
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Grovyle is highly intelligent and can differentiate the cries of various Pokémon. It is agile and can easily maneuver through the trees.

pokemonDataList.name: Sceptile
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Sceptile is a highly agile Pokémon, known for its incredible speed and sharp claws. It is very adept at jumping and climbing, thriving in forested environments.

pokemonDataList.name: Torchic
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Torchic has a fire sac in its belly. When it gets angry, the sac overheats and begins to glow. It is said that this Pokémon can breathe fire from its mouth as hot as 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemonDataList.name: Combusken
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Combusken is a fierce Pokémon that can quickly kick with both legs. It can also roast its opponents with its fiery tail.

pokemonDataList.name: Blaziken
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Blaziken is known for its fiery kicks, which can set its opponents ablaze. Its high-speed attacks are complemented by its powerful Fire and Fighting-type moves.

pokemonDataList.name: Mudkip
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Mudkip is a Water-type Pokémon. It is known for its ability to adapt to a variety of environments. Its tail fin is used to propel itself through water with great speed.

pokemonDataList.name: Marshtomp
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Marshtomp's sturdy legs provide strong traction. It can swim with ease, thanks to its amphibious nature. It is very skilled at mud-slinging.

pokemonDataList.name: Swampert
pokemonDataList.pokedexEntry: Swampert's arms are the best tools for digging. It is very capable in water, with excellent swimming abilities and adaptability.
